about.summary: Recently many new p-value based multiple test procedures have been proposed, and these new methods are more powerful than the widely used Hochberg procedure. These procedures strongly control the familywise error rate (FWER). This is a comprehensive collection of p-value based FWER-control stepwise multiple test procedures, including six procedure families and thirty multiple test procedures. In this collection, the conservative Hochberg procedure, linear time Hommel procedures, asymptotic Rom procedure, Gou-Tamhane-Xi-Rom procedures, and Quick procedures are all developed in recent five years since 2014. The package name "elitism" is an acronym of "e"quipment for "l"ogarithmic and l"i"near "ti"me "s"tepwise "m"ultiple hypothesis testing. Version 1.0.0 was released on June 26, 2019. See Gou, J., and Zhang, F. (2020). Quick multiple test procedures and p-value adjustments. Technical report.

name: r-elitism
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '1.0.4' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-elitism
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/elitism_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/elitism/elitism_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: f97d79074906aa41f0c78d232a0cb8e941d53d0d6a0b85cd61bcb4169a0daf58

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-mass
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-mass

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('elitism')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('elitism')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=elitism
  license: GPL-3.0-only
  summary: Recently many new p-value based multiple test procedures have been proposed, and these
    new methods are more powerful than the widely used Hochberg procedure. These procedures
    strongly control the familywise error rate (FWER). This is a comprehensive collection
    of p-value based FWER-control stepwise multiple test procedures, including six procedure
    families and thirty multiple test procedures. In this collection, the conservative
    Hochberg procedure, linear time Hommel procedures, asymptotic Rom procedure, Gou-Tamhane-Xi-Rom
    procedures, and Quick procedures are all developed in recent five years since 2014.
    The package name "elitism" is an acronym of "e"quipment for "l"ogarithmic and l"i"near
    "ti"me "s"tepwise "m"ultiple hypothesis testing. Version 1.0.0 was released on June
    26, 2019. See Gou, J., and Zhang, F. (2020). Quick multiple test procedures and
    p-value adjustments. Technical report.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
